National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice has released a statement regarding the release of U.S. citizen Peter Theo Curtis, who was held hostage in Syria for two years. The statement expresses joy and relief for Curtis' freedom and mentions that he is now safe outside of Syria. Rice also mentions that efforts will continue to free the remaining Americans held captive in Syria. The statement concludes by expressing gratitude for the support and prayers of the American people and the hope for the safe return of all Americans held overseas.